article.headline: Columbia beats St. Francis (NY) 81-61
article.story: NEW YORK -- Maodo Lo scored 22 points Saturday and Alex Rosenberg added 21 as Columbia rolled over St. Francis (NY) 81-61, snapping the Terriers' four-game win streak. Lo opened the game with a layup and Columbia jumped to a 15-2 lead, led 50-33 at halftime and never looked back. The Lions (9-6) shot 55.2 percent from the field in the first half to just 34.4 percent for the Terriers (9-6), and 63.6 percent from beyond the arc (7 of 11). Grant Mullins scored 11 points for the Lions and Isaac Cohen grabbed 10 rebounds. Rosenberg has reached double figures in scoring 10 games in a row. The Lions finished with 10 3-pointers on 22 attempts (45.5 percent), and the team has made 250 treys this season, shattering the school's single-season mark of 218 set in 1996-97. Jalen Cannon and Ben Mockford scored 15 apiece for the Terriers and Lowell Ulmer added 12.
